# title: Alexander Gradsky / Александр Градский 1976-78
# date:  2010-07-29 09:41:39
# tags:  gradsky, 70s, progressive

[img/russkie-pesni.jpg]
Александр Градский и группа “Скоморохи”
LP Русские песни (Translates as “Russian Songs”)
Melodiya / Мелодия C60-14621 / recorded 1976-78, released 1980

Recently an anonymous guest asked where are the following tunes from. They are from this album. Thank you for reminding me of it. Now I like it more than 0.5 years ago.

It's the same Alexander Gradsky who wrote these <a href="/garanian-the-melodia-ensemble-romance-for-lovers-ost-1974.html">unbelievable hard killer funk breaks from “Romance for Lovers”</a>.

I believe the music has some relation to progressive rock, so Darius — you probably could find it interesting.

[other/russkie-pesni-sampler.mp3] 

Tracklisting:
01. Ничто в полюшке
02. Дарю платок (страдания)
03. Таня белая (хоровод танок)
04. Плач
05. На Ивана Купала
06. Не одна в поле дороженька
07. Солдатская
08. Вы жертвою пали

